accounts of the witch operations, but he seems to
regard negro testimony as unreliable and declines
to quote their savings; on general principles no
doubt. But in this the good man is mistaken.
He has not studied the negro character along this
line. The colored brether may prevaricate in
regard to a chicken roost; he may be extravagant
