about the golden pavements in the New Jerusalem
and the angels sopping possum gravy with ash
cakes and "taters;" he may mislead one in regard
to the contents of his gourd bottle; he may be
weak on the subject of watermellons, and tell fine
stories on Bre'r Rabbit sitting in the fence corner
picking briars out of his feet, but when it comes
